comment.body:
This block currently creates a stack allocated object, does a memcopy of ip and gateway, takes a reference to the stack allocation for the comparison, removes the stack allocation, and if the ip is not found, creates an exactly new stack allocation with similar content, and moves it to the heap in the vec. This can both be written more concise and slightly more performant by first creating the standalone PublicIP object, and then working with said object:

```
let publicIP = PublicIP {
    ip: ip.ip,
    gateway: ip.gw,
    contract_id: 0,
};

if public_ips_list.contains(&publicIP) { return Err(...) };
public_ips_list.try_push(publicIP).or_else(...);
```

