comment.body:
Other node with this problem: 4200. graphql query to get 3 uptime events which are not in line:

```graphql
query MyQuery {
  uptimeEvents(where: {nodeID_eq: 4200, timestamp_gte: "1666599918", timestamp_lte: "1666844640"}, orderBy: timestamp_DESC) {
    uptime
    timestamp
  }
}
```

The 2nd data point reports considerably less uptime compared to increase in timestamp (-1999 seconds), the third (newest) compared to the second reports a bit more uptime compared to timestamp difference (+303 seconds).

Additionally, this node seems to have other instances of this occurring more recently. Of particular instance is this event:

```graphql
query MyQuery {
  uptimeEvents(where: {nodeID_eq: 4200, timestamp_gte: "1669545036", timestamp_lte: "1669553322"}, orderBy: timestamp_DESC) {
    uptime
    timestamp
  }
}
```

where the third (newest) event actually has a positive drift (uptime increases more than timestamp) of 367 seconds, without a significant prior negative drift.

